<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<model version="NetLogo 7.0.3" snapToGrid="true">
  <code><![CDATA[;; ABOUTME: Topology tournament demo comparing mesh, hierarchy, and chain
;; ABOUTME: communication structures for per-agent LLM-driven collective convergence

extensions [llm]

breed [mesh-agents mesh-agent]
breed [hierarchy-agents hierarchy-agent]
breed [chain-agents chain-agent]
undirected-link-breed [topology-links topology-link]

globals [
  llm-ready?
  tournament-running?
  topology-order
  convergence-times
  winner-topology
  belief-options
]

turtles-own [
  belief
  previous-belief
  topology-name
  rounds-unchanged
]

to setup
  clear-all

  set llm-ready? false
  set tournament-running? true
  set topology-order ["mesh" "hierarchy" "chain"]
  set convergence-times (list -1 -1 -1)
  set winner-topology "pending"
  set belief-options ["COLLECT" "EXPLORE" "STABILIZE"]

  load-llm-config
  build-topologies
  seed-beliefs
  initialize-agents

  reset-ticks
end

to load-llm-config
  carefully [
    llm:load-config llm-config-path
    set llm-ready? true
  ] [
    print (word "LLM config load failed: " error-message)
    print "Falling back to deterministic coordinator policy."
    set llm-ready? false
  ]
end

to build-topologies
  build-mesh-topology
  build-hierarchy-topology
  build-chain-topology

  ask topology-links [
    set color gray - 2
    set thickness 0.1
  ]
end

to build-mesh-topology
  create-mesh-agents agents-per-topology [
    set topology-name "mesh"
    set shape "circle"
    set color blue + 1
    set size 1.3
  ]

  layout-circle mesh-agents 6
  ask mesh-agents [
    set xcor xcor - 16
    set ycor ycor + 8
  ]

  let ordered sort mesh-agents
  foreach (range length ordered) [i ->
    let source item i ordered
    foreach (range (i + 1) (length ordered)) [j ->
      let target item j ordered
      ask source [ create-topology-link-with target ]
    ]
  ]
end

to build-hierarchy-topology
  create-hierarchy-agents agents-per-topology [
    set topology-name "hierarchy"
    set shape "triangle"
    set color green + 1
    set size 1.4
  ]

  let ordered sort hierarchy-agents
  foreach (range length ordered) [i ->
    let level floor (ln (i + 1) / ln 2)
    let first-at-level ((2 ^ level) - 1)
    let level-position (i - first-at-level)
    let level-width (2 ^ level)
    let x-offset (level-position - ((level-width - 1) / 2)) * 3
    let y-offset 14 - (level * 4)

    ask item i ordered [
      setxy x-offset y-offset
    ]

    if i > 0 [
      let parent-index floor ((i - 1) / 2)
      let parent-node item parent-index ordered
      ask item i ordered [ create-topology-link-with parent-node ]
    ]
  ]
end

to build-chain-topology
  create-chain-agents agents-per-topology [
    set topology-name "chain"
    set shape "square"
    set color orange + 1
    set size 1.3
  ]

  let ordered sort chain-agents
  let spacing 2.8
  let start-x (16 - ((agents-per-topology - 1) * spacing / 2))

  foreach (range length ordered) [i ->
    ask item i ordered [
      setxy (start-x + (i * spacing)) -12
    ]

    if i > 0 [
      let prev-node item (i - 1) ordered
      ask item i ordered [ create-topology-link-with prev-node ]
    ]
  ]
end

to seed-beliefs
  assign-beliefs mesh-agents 0
  assign-beliefs hierarchy-agents 1
  assign-beliefs chain-agents 2

  ask turtles [
    set label (word topology-name ":" belief)
    set label-color white
  ]
end

to assign-beliefs [group shift]
  let ordered sort group
  foreach (range length ordered) [i ->
    let slot ((i + shift) mod length belief-options)
    ask item i ordered [
      set belief item slot belief-options
    ]
  ]
end

to initialize-agents
  ask turtles [
    set previous-belief belief
    set rounds-unchanged 0
  ]
end

to go
  if not tournament-running? [ stop ]

  ;; Snapshot beliefs for simultaneous update
  ask turtles [ set previous-belief belief ]

  ;; Each unconverged agent decides independently
  ask turtles [
    let idx position topology-name topology-order
    if item idx convergence-times = -1 [
      decide-belief
    ]
  ]

  check-all-convergence
  update-tournament-state
  tick
end

to decide-belief
  let neighbor-beliefs [previous-belief] of link-neighbors
  if empty? neighbor-beliefs [ stop ]

  ifelse use-llm? and llm-ready?
  [ decide-belief-llm neighbor-beliefs ]
  [ decide-belief-deterministic neighbor-beliefs ]

  ifelse belief = previous-belief
  [ set rounds-unchanged rounds-unchanged + 1 ]
  [ set rounds-unchanged 0 ]

  set label (word topology-name ":" belief)
end

to decide-belief-llm [neighbor-beliefs]
  carefully [
    ;; Reset history each tick to prevent unbounded token growth
    llm:set-history (list
      (list "system" (word
        "You are agent " who " in a " topology-name " network. "
        "Choose the belief that will help your group reach consensus fastest. "
        "Prefer the majority belief among your neighbors if one exists."
      ))
    )
    let prompt (word
      "Your belief: " belief ". "
      "Neighbor beliefs: " belief-count-summary neighbor-beliefs ". "
      "Which belief?"
    )
    set belief llm:choose prompt belief-options
  ] [
    decide-belief-deterministic neighbor-beliefs
  ]
end

to decide-belief-deterministic [neighbor-beliefs]
  let all-local lput belief neighbor-beliefs
  let best belief
  let best-count 0
  foreach belief-options [candidate ->
    let cnt length filter [b -> b = candidate] all-local
    if cnt > best-count [ set best candidate  set best-count cnt ]
  ]
  set belief best
end

to-report belief-count-summary [belief-list]
  let chunks []
  foreach belief-options [candidate ->
    let cnt length filter [b -> b = candidate] belief-list
    if cnt > 0 [ set chunks lput (word candidate ":" cnt) chunks ]
  ]
  ifelse empty? chunks [ report "none" ]
  [ report reduce [[a b] -> word a ", " b] chunks ]
end

to check-all-convergence
  check-topology-convergence "mesh" mesh-agents
  check-topology-convergence "hierarchy" hierarchy-agents
  check-topology-convergence "chain" chain-agents
end

to check-topology-convergence [name group]
  let idx position name topology-order
  if item idx convergence-times != -1 [ stop ]
  if converged? group [
    set convergence-times replace-item idx convergence-times ticks
  ]
end

to-report converged? [group]
  if not any? group [ report false ]
  report (length remove-duplicates [belief] of group) = 1
end

to-report majority-belief [group]
  let best-belief first belief-options
  let best-count -1

  foreach belief-options [candidate ->
    let candidate-count count group with [belief = candidate]
    if candidate-count > best-count [
      set best-belief candidate
      set best-count candidate-count
    ]
  ]

  report best-belief
end

to-report belief-summary [group]
  let chunks []
  foreach belief-options [candidate ->
    set chunks lput (word candidate ":" count group with [belief = candidate]) chunks
  ]
  report reduce [[left right] -> word left ", " right] chunks
end

to update-tournament-state
  if all? convergence-times [value -> value >= 0] [
    set tournament-running? false
    set winner-topology fastest-topology
    stop
  ]

  if ticks >= max-ticks [
    set tournament-running? false
    set winner-topology fastest-topology
  ]
end

to-report fastest-topology
  let best-name "none"
  let best-time (max-ticks + 1)

  foreach (range length topology-order) [i ->
    let result item i convergence-times
    if result != -1 and result < best-time [
      set best-time result
      set best-name item i topology-order
    ]
  ]

  report best-name
end

to-report agreement-pct [group]
  if not any? group [ report 0 ]
  let majority majority-belief group
  report 100 * (count group with [belief = majority]) / count group
end

to-report convergence-time [name]
  report item (position name topology-order) convergence-times
end

to-report status-summary
  report (word
    "mesh=" convergence-time "mesh"
    " hierarchy=" convergence-time "hierarchy"
    " chain=" convergence-time "chain"
    " winner=" winner-topology
  )
end

to-report llm-status
  ifelse use-llm? and llm-ready?
  [ report "Connected" ]
  [ report "Deterministic" ]
end]]></code>
  <widgets>
    <view x="210" y="10" width="820" height="620"
          minPxcor="-25" maxPxcor="25" minPycor="-25" maxPycor="25"
          patchSize="12.0" wrappingAllowedX="false" wrappingAllowedY="false"
          fontSize="10" updateMode="1" showTickCounter="true" tickCounterLabel="ticks" frameRate="30.0"></view>
    <button x="15" y="10" width="90" height="33"
            display="Setup" source="observer" forever="false">setup</button>
    <button x="15" y="50" width="90" height="33"
            display="Go" source="observer" forever="true">go</button>
    <button x="110" y="50" width="90" height="33"
            display="Step" source="observer" forever="false">go</button>
    <slider x="15" y="110" width="195" height="33"
            display="agents-per-topology" variable="agents-per-topology"
            min="3" max="12" default="6.0" step="1" units="" direction="horizontal"></slider>
    <slider x="15" y="150" width="195" height="33"
            display="max-ticks" variable="max-ticks"
            min="20" max="400" default="150.0" step="1" units="" direction="horizontal"></slider>
    <inputBox x="15" y="195" width="195" height="60"
              variable="llm-config-path" multiline="false" type="String">demos/topology-tournament/config.txt</inputBox>
    <switch x="830" y="210" width="280" height="33"
            display="use-llm?" variable="use-llm?" on="true"></switch>
    <monitor x="830" y="250" width="280" height="33"
             display="LLM Status" source="observer" precision="17">llm-status</monitor>
    <monitor x="15" y="270" width="195" height="33"
             display="Winner" source="observer" precision="17">winner-topology</monitor>
    <monitor x="15" y="310" width="195" height="33"
             display="Status" source="observer" precision="17">status-summary</monitor>
    <monitor x="15" y="350" width="195" height="33"
             display="Mesh Convergence" source="observer" precision="0">convergence-time "mesh"</monitor>
    <monitor x="15" y="390" width="195" height="33"
             display="Hierarchy Convergence" source="observer" precision="0">convergence-time "hierarchy"</monitor>
    <monitor x="15" y="430" width="195" height="33"
             display="Chain Convergence" source="observer" precision="0">convergence-time "chain"</monitor>
    <monitor x="830" y="290" width="280" height="33"
             display="Mesh Agreement %" source="observer" precision="1">agreement-pct mesh-agents</monitor>
    <monitor x="830" y="330" width="280" height="33"
             display="Hierarchy Agreement %" source="observer" precision="1">agreement-pct hierarchy-agents</monitor>
    <monitor x="830" y="370" width="280" height="33"
             display="Chain Agreement %" source="observer" precision="1">agreement-pct chain-agents</monitor>
    <plot x="830" y="10" width="280" height="190"
          display="Agreement by Topology" xAxis="Ticks" yAxis="Agreement %"
          xMin="0.0" xMax="100.0" yMin="0.0" yMax="100.0"
          autoPlotOn="true" legendOn="true" setupCode="" updateCode="">
      <pen name="mesh" interval="1.0" mode="0" color="-13345367" inLegend="true"
           setupCode="" updateCode="plot agreement-pct mesh-agents"></pen>
      <pen name="hierarchy" interval="1.0" mode="0" color="-10899396" inLegend="true"
           setupCode="" updateCode="plot agreement-pct hierarchy-agents"></pen>
      <pen name="chain" interval="1.0" mode="0" color="-955883" inLegend="true"
           setupCode="" updateCode="plot agreement-pct chain-agents"></pen>
    </plot>
  </widgets>
  <info><![CDATA[## WHAT IS IT?

This model compares three communication topologies — **mesh**, **hierarchy**, and **chain** — in a collective coordination task. Each agent independently observes only its `link-neighbors` and uses `llm:choose` (or a deterministic local-majority fallback) to pick a belief. Topology genuinely constrains information flow, replicating the MARBLE paper's core finding that network structure affects convergence speed.

The question: when agents can only see their direct neighbors, does network structure determine how quickly a group reaches consensus?

## HOW IT WORKS

Each tick follows this cycle:

1. **Snapshot** — all agents save their current belief to `previous-belief` (simultaneous update semantics).
2. **Decide** — each unconverged agent gathers its `link-neighbors`' snapshotted beliefs, then:
   - **LLM mode**: calls `llm:set-history` with a per-agent system prompt, then `llm:choose` to pick from the belief options.
   - **Deterministic mode**: applies local majority rule (self + neighbors; ties broken by current belief).
3. **Check convergence** — if all agents in a topology share one belief, record the tick.
4. **Update tournament** — when all topologies converge or `max-ticks` is reached, declare a winner.

**Why topology matters**: Mesh agents have degree n-1 (see all peers), hierarchy agents have degree 1-3 (parent + children), and chain agents have degree 1-2 (left + right neighbors). Higher connectivity means more information per decision, leading to faster convergence.

The tournament ends when all three topologies have converged, or `max-ticks` is reached.

## HOW TO USE IT

1. Set `llm-config-path` to a valid config file (default points to `demos/topology-tournament/config.txt`).
2. Add a real API key in the config file.
3. Click **Setup** to build topologies and seed beliefs.
4. Click **Go** for continuous execution, or **Step** for single-tick stepping.
5. Toggle **use-llm?** to switch between LLM-driven and deterministic per-agent decisions.
6. Watch convergence monitors (left panel) and agreement-percentage monitors (right panel).
7. The **Agreement by Topology** plot shows real-time convergence curves.
8. **LLM Status** monitor shows "Connected" or "Deterministic".

## THINGS TO NOTICE

- **Mesh** converges fastest because each agent sees all peers (degree n-1) — full information every tick.
- **Hierarchy** converges in the middle: agents near the root see more neighbors, but leaf agents see only their parent.
- **Chain** is the slowest because each agent sees at most 2 neighbors — information propagates one hop per tick.
- In deterministic mode, the local-majority rule makes topology differences especially visible since there is no LLM reasoning to compensate for limited visibility.
- With LLM mode on, agents may make more strategic choices, but the topology constraint still limits what they can observe.

## THINGS TO TRY

- Toggle **use-llm?** on and off between runs to compare LLM vs deterministic convergence speeds.
- Vary **agents-per-topology** from 3 to 12 and observe how group size affects convergence time.
- Change the model in `config.txt` (e.g., `gpt-4o` vs `gpt-4o-mini`) and compare LLM decision quality.
- Increase **max-ticks** to give slower topologies more time to converge.
- Run multiple trials and note whether the winner is consistent.

## EXTENDING THE MODEL

- Add a **ring** or **star** topology for additional comparison.
- Give agents memory of past rounds so beliefs evolve over longer time horizons.
- Add noise: randomly flip one agent's belief each tick to test robustness.
- Let agents weight neighbor opinions differently based on how long neighbors have held their beliefs.
- Experiment with different LLM temperature settings to vary decision randomness.

## NETLOGO FEATURES

- **`llm:choose`** constrains the LLM to select from a fixed list of belief options.
- **`llm:set-history`** sets per-agent conversation context, reset each tick to prevent token growth.
- **`link-neighbors`** provides topology-aware neighbor queries — each agent only sees directly connected peers.
- **Simultaneous update** via `previous-belief` snapshot ensures agents decide from the same time-step state.
- **Breeds** (`mesh-agents`, `hierarchy-agents`, `chain-agents`) separate agents by topology.
- **`foreach (range ...)`** replaces imperative while-loops for cleaner iteration.
- **`position name topology-order`** replaces a manual if-chain for topology index lookup.

## CREDITS AND REFERENCES

Inspired by the MARBLE paper (arXiv:2503.01935) on how network topology affects multi-agent LLM convergence. Part of the NetLogo LLM Extension demo suite. See the [extension README](../../README.md) for setup and API documentation.]]></info>
